!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

aspect /ˈæspɛkt/

(aspects) 

1. N-COUNT An aspect of something is one of the parts of its character or nature. 方面 

例： Climate and weather affect every aspect of our lives. 气候和天气影响我们生活的每个方面。 

例： He was interested in all aspects of the work here. 他对这里工作的各方面都感兴趣。 

2. N-COUNT The aspect of a building or window is the direction in which it faces. (建筑物或窗子的) 朝向 [正式] 

例： The house had a southwest aspect. 这房子为西南朝向。

</div>

